article.headline: Ohio 90, W. Michigan 74
article.story: ATHENS, Ohio -- Tommy Freeman scored a career-high 30 points and tied a career-best with six 3-pointers, leading Ohio past Western Michigan 90-74 on Tuesday night. Armon Bassett added 21 points, including five 3s, and a career-high nine assists for the Bobcats (13-11, 4-6 Mid-American Conference), who hit a season-high 14 of 23 3-pointers (60.9 percent) in the win. The Broncos finished just 8 of 23 from long range (34.8 percent). Kenneth Van Kempen finished with 12 points and D.J. Cooper added 11 for Ohio. Western Michigan got a pair of early 3s for a 6-2 lead, but Freeman hit his first 3-pointer of the game for Ohio, sparking a 10-0 run, and the Bobcats didn't trail again. Ohio led by 20 points at halftime and held on despite being outscored by the Broncos 49-45 in the second. Martelle McLemore tied his career high with 24 points for the Broncos (13-11, 5-6).
